                  "name": "Monster Core pg. 44",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Monster Core",
                "page": 44,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Boggards prefer to dwell in swamplands and mires. Though they are at home in the water, they prefer to spend most of their lives on land and build villages of mud huts. They often keep guardian beasts, such as crocodiles, giant frogs, or other feral animals tamed (if only just barely) to serve as protectors.",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "links": [
              {
                "alt": "Gogunta",
                "aonid": 25,
                "game-obj": "Deities",
                "name": "Gogunta",
                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Gogunta",
            "sources": [
              {
                "errata": {
                  "alt": "1.1",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "1.1",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Monster Core pg. 44",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Monster Core pg. 44",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Monster Core",
                "page": 44,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Gogunta is the patron of the boggard people, many of whom worship her as their goddess.",
            "type": "section"
          }
        ],
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "1.1",
              "aonid": 221,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "1.1",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Monster Core pg. 44",
              "aonid": 221,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Monster Core pg. 44",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Monster Core",
            "page": 44,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Boggards are aggressive humanoid amphibians who thrive in swamps, marshes, and even some rain forests. Boggards hatch from eggs into tadpoles, fiercely competing for food and even consuming their siblings in that struggle. Over 3 years, the surviving boggards develop arms, legs, and lungs while learning the rudiments of hunting, crafts, and warfare\u2014everything needed to survive in their might-makes-right society. At the top of most boggard hierarchies lords a hulking swampseer imbued with sinister divine magic.",
        "type": "monster_family"
      },
